CSCE 451/851 Homework 3 - Problem 1
Sleeping Stylist with Semaphores

Team members:
Karnav Patel

Build:
make

Run:
./sleepingStylistSem

What to observe:
The program creates 120 customer threads and one stylist thread. The stylist
starts first, so the output shows the stylist going to sleep when the salon is
empty. Customers then arrive, sit in the seven waiting chairs, leave to go
shopping when the salon is full, and retry until every customer receives a
haircut.

The chair line uses the required form:
| 1 | 1 | 1 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | => 3

The output also reports:
Given haircuts = number of completed haircuts
Salon full = counter incremented by 7 each time the seventh chair is filled
Salon empty = number of times the stylist goes to sleep

Time spent:
Problem 1: about 5 hours.

Challenge level:
Problem 1: 3 out of 5.
